<title>USA: Monarch Pharmaceuticals buys Glaxo product.</title>
<headline>Monarch Pharmaceuticals buys Glaxo product.</headline>
<dateline>BRISTOL, Tenn. 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Monarch Pharmaceuticals said Friday it bought the U.S. rights to Viroptic, a Glaxo Wellcome Plc product for treating inflammation of the cornea caused by the herpes simplex virus.</p>
<p>The company did not disclose the purchase price.</p>
<p>Monarch is a wholly-owned subsidiary of King Pharmaceuticals Inc, which is a privately-held company.</p>
